Ondo Governor Rotimi Akeredolu has appointed Temitayo Oluwatuyi as the new Secretary to the State Government. Oluwatuyi takes over from Ifedayo Abegunde, who resigned his appointment on Monday. The Governor disclosed this via his verified Twitter handle. The appointment, according to him, is with immediate effect. “Today, I announced the appointment of Hon. Temitayo Oluwatuyi “Tukana” as the Secretary to the State Government (SSG) to resume immediately following the resignation of Hon. Ifedayo Abegunde,” Akeredolu tweeted. Details shortly…